    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-12-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-12-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="167"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d167">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">422.11G93/1154 1/2</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hartman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-12-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 20, 1920</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received January 15, 1921.]</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 624</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to confirm my telegram No. 84 of
                    December 18, 12 noon,<note n="32" xml:id="d167fn32">Not printed.</note>
                    reporting total deposits as of December 15, 1920, on account of service of
                    Guayaquil &amp; Quito Railway bonds, and Salt Certificates. The exact amounts of
                    such deposits follow: <table cols="2" rows="2">
                        <row>
                            <cell rend="padding-left: 2em;">For service of Guayaquil &amp; Quito
                                Railway bonds</cell>
                            <cell role="num">S/.404,954.47</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell rend="padding-left: 2em;">For Salt Certificates</cell>
                            <cell role="num">93,866.40</cell>
                        </row>
                    </table>
                </p>
                <p>I further report that no remittances to London have been made.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Chas. S. Hartman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
